(1024, 1, '2019-05-22 03:42:08', '2019-05-22 03:42:08', '[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1481579717819{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 40px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_custom_heading text="What is Sustainability?" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:30px|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes"][vc_custom_heading text="sustainable enterprises and the Work Integrated Program." font_container="tag:h3|text_align:left|color:%234145ee" use_theme_fonts="yes"][vc_column_text]\n<div class="copyContainer">According to research, this is what keeps owners, executives, &amp; directors awake at night</div>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_btn title="Read More"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_progress_bar values="%5B%7B%22value%22%3A%2242%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22custom%22%2C%22customcolor%22%3A%22%234145ee%22%2C%22customtxtcolor%22%3A%22%23ffffff%22%7D%5D" bgcolor="custom" options="striped,animated" units="%" custombgcolor="#ffffff" title="Sustainability and long term growth prospects" customtxtcolor="#ffffff" css=".vc_custom_1558427455117{margin-bottom: 25px !important;}"][vc_progress_bar values="%5B%7B%22value%22%3A%2228%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22custom%22%2C%22customcolor%22%3A%22%234145ee%22%2C%22customtxtcolor%22%3A%22%23ffffff%22%7D%5D" bgcolor="custom" options="striped,animated" units="%" custombgcolor="#ffffff" title="Structural change/changing business models" customtxtcolor="#ffffff" css=".vc_custom_1558427472855{margin-bottom: 25px !important;}"][vc_progress_bar values="%5B%7B%22value%22%3A%2221%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22custom%22%2C%22customcolor%22%3A%22%234145ee%22%2C%22customtxtcolor%22%3A%22%23ffffff%22%7D%5D" bgcolor="custom" options="striped,animated" units="%" custombgcolor="#ffffff" title="Legal and regulatory compliance" customtxtcolor="#ffffff" css=".vc_custom_1558427486914{margin-bottom: 25px !important;}"][vc_progress_bar values="%5B%7B%22value%22%3A%2220%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22custom%22%2C%22customcolor%22%3A%22%234145ee%22%2C%22customtxtcolor%22%3A%22%23ffffff%22%7D%5D" bgcolor="custom" options="striped,animated" units="%" custombgcolor="#ffffff" title="The remaining 16 issues (from 20% down to 3%)" customtxtcolor="#ffffff" css=".vc_custom_1558427501293{margin-bottom: 25px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" css=".vc_custom_1481580715078{padding-top: 40px !important;padding-bottom: 40px !important;background-color: #ffffff !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_custom_heading text="Strategic Sustainability & Risk Management (SS&RM)" google_fonts="font_family:Arvo%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_column_text]\n<div class="copyContainer">Over the last decade or so, many sustainability and risk management frameworks have been developed to incorporate concepts in business, social justice, governance, and political systems. This document looks at the development of sustainability from the perspectives of ERM (enterprise risk management), TBL (triple bottom line), CSR (corporate social responsibility) and SE (sustainable enterprise) to develop a workable business model that is realistic and easy to implement.</div>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_btn title="Read More"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1558428770176{padding-left: 90px !important;}"][vc_line_chart type="line" style="modern" x_values="2007; 2011; 2015; 2019;" values="%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Strategic%20Sustainability%22%2C%22y_values%22%3A%223%3B%205%3B%209%3B%2010%3B%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22blue%22%2C%22custom_color%22%3A%22%233d50eb%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Risk%20Management%22%2C%22y_values%22%3A%222%3B%206%3B%204%3B%208%3B%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22pink%22%2C%22custom_color%22%3A%22%235a6aee%22%7D%5D"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][ultimate_heading main_heading="Strategic Sustainability & Risk Management (SS&RM) "]SME Enterprises, Registered Clubs, NFP Organizations[/ultimate_heading][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1558431218204{margin-top: 40px !important;}"]\n<div class="copyContainer"><span style="color: #808080;">Ian Kirkwood is a business academic specialising in strategic sustainability and corporate responsibility. His career includes more than 30 years in engineering, business development and executive roles plus the last 10 years in training and academia. He interfaces with a range of local and international businesses.</span></div>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/6"][vc_custom_heading text="Opposition" font_container="tag:h2|text_align:center|color:%235472d2" google_fonts="font_family:Arvo%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_icon type="linecons" icon_linecons="vc_li vc_li-clock" size="lg" align="center"][vc_column_text]\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Rejection</strong>\nCSR claims seems as illegitimate for corporation\n\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][vc_custom_heading text="Ignorance" font_container="tag:h2|text_align:center|color:%235472d2" google_fonts="font_family:Arvo%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_icon type="linecons" icon_linecons="vc_li vc_li-tv" size="lg" align="center"][vc_column_text]\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Rejection</strong>\nCSR claims seems as illegitimate for corporation\n\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][vc_custom_heading text="Risk" font_container="tag:h2|text_align:center|color:%235472d2" google_fonts="font_family:Arvo%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_icon type="linecons" icon_linecons="vc_li vc_li-fire" size="lg" align="center"][vc_column_text]\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Rejection</strong>\nCSR claims seems as illegitimate for corporation\n\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][vc_custom_heading text="Cost" font_container="tag:h2|text_align:center|color:%235472d2" google_fonts="font_family:Arvo%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_icon type="linecons" icon_linecons="vc_li vc_li-vallet" size="lg" align="center"][vc_column_text]\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Rejection</strong>\nCSR claims seems as illegitimate for corporation\n\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][vc_custom_heading text="Competitive Advance" font_container="tag:h2|text_align:center|color:%235472d2" google_fonts="font_family:Arvo%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_icon type="linecons" icon_linecons="vc_li vc_li-paperplane" size="lg" align="center"][vc_column_text]\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Rejection</strong>\nCSR claims seems as illegitimate for corporation\n\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][vc_custom_heading text="Transformation" font_container="tag:h2|text_align:center|color:%235472d2" google_fonts="font_family:Arvo%3Aregular%2Citalic%2C700%2C700italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_icon type="linecons" icon_linecons="vc_li vc_li-lab" size="lg" align="center"][vc_column_text]\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Rejection</strong>\nCSR claims seems as illegitimate for corporation\n\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" css=".vc_custom_1558495968523{background-color: #ffffff !important;}"][vc_column][ultimate_heading main_heading="Sustainability"][/ultimate_heading][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1558495982799{margin-top: 40px !important;}"]\n<div class="copyContainer"><span style="color: #808080;">Business and economic sustainability is considered essential for survival of the human race and for the maintenance of the earth as a habitable environment. Damage is being caused by businesses and that damage needs to be stopped, prevented, and repaired if life as it is currently understood is to prevail. Businesses are a part of modern global society and collectively we owe our existence and survival to the life giving sources of the earth. Hence business activities and outputs must be seen from an eco-social perspective more than they need to be seen from a simple economic perspective. This notwithstanding, businesses certainly have an economic imperative however this imperative is for people in general and not for the business per se. People need the planet to sustain life so that any planet-damaging business activities are therefore not in the best interests of the very people the business is economically serving. Therefore businesses are only valid if they truly serve their primary purposes first and foremost and their economic interests second. For businesses to transform to a new paradigm and stay viable, the following four point plan is considered essential for their development and possibly their survival. A new business paradigm, or zeitgeist, is certainly essential for the survival of humanity as we know it.</span></div>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Sustainability', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '381-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-05-22 03:42:08', '2019-05-22 03:42:08', '', 381, 'http://jcucms.x10host.com/team007/2019/05/22/381-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
